Preconditions:
- The input list `maxHeights` must not be null.
- The length of the input list `maxHeights` must be greater than 0.
- Each element in the input list `maxHeights` must be a positive integer.

Postconditions:
- The method returns a long value representing the maximum possible sum of heights of a beautiful configuration of towers.
- The returned sum of heights is greater than or equal to 0.
- The returned sum of heights is the maximum possible sum among all beautiful configurations of towers.